    "### Data overview\n",
    "\n",
    "An ideal dataset: For an ideal dataset for this project, we would want at least 1000 observations. Data would include information relating to CPU, GPU, and RAM requirements for PC games released from 2010 to 2020. Such features would have data on type(s) and/or costs of the hardware mentioned. For our dataset, we would be looking for data collected by Valve and other sources that webscraped the Steam page for hardware requirements, like Kaggle. We would store and organize the data we find as a CSV file which would make it easy to analyze and make visualizations for our data.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Dataset #1\n",
    "  - Dataset Name: Video Games Computer Requirements\n",
    "  - Link to the dataset: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/baraazaid/pc-video-game-requirements-v2?resource=download\n",
    "  - Number of observations: 10843\n",
    "  - Number of variables: 90\n",
    "  - Description of the variables most relevant to this project\n",
    "    - Min_CPU_CPU_Speed - the minimum speed of the CPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_CPU_Turbo_Speed - the minimum turbo speed of the CPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_CPU_Physical_Cores - the minimum number of physical cores of the CPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_CPU_Threads - the minimum number of threads of the CPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_CPU_GD_Rating - the minimum GD rating of the CPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Shader - the minimum shader version of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Direct_X - the minimum version of Direct X required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Memory - the minimum memory of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_GD_RATING - the minimum GD rating of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Boost_Clock - the minimum boost clock of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Memory_Bandwidth - the minimum memory bandwidth of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_GPU_Process - the minimum process of the GPU required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_RAM - the minimum amount of RAM required to run the game\n",
    "    - Min_VRAM - the minimum amount of VRAM required to run the game\n",
    "  - Descriptions of any shortcomings this dataset has with respect to the project\n",
    "    - Some of the data of the variables are stored as objects with the number and units, so when analyzing it, we would have to change it to int values.\n",
    "    - Some of the categories are not usually what games recommend for their gameplay, but are engineering specs.\n",
    "    - Some of the columns in this dataset are seen to be correlated with other columns.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
